article.headline: North Dakota 66, Idaho St. 53
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho -- Aaron Anderson hit three 3-pointers and scored 19 points Thursday night, helping North Dakota to a 66-53 victory over Idaho State. Troy Huff added 15 points and Josh Schuler had 14 for North Dakota(4-8, 1-2 Big Sky), and Jordan Allard pulled down 10 rebounds. Both teams shot just 40 percent from the field, but North Dakota dominated the boards, outrebounding Idaho State 43-22. Tomas Sanchez scored 15 for the Bengals (1-11, 0-3), who lost their sixth in a row. Andre Hatchett chipped in 11 points, and Chris Hansen had 10 points and four steals. North Dakota never trailed and led 31-9 before the Bengals closed the first half on an 11-0 run. But Idaho State couldn't close the gap after halftime. North Dakota took a 2-1 lead in the all-time series; the teams met for the first time last season and split their two games.
